The paper deals with the problem of approximating the densest subgraph in a dynamic graph stream model, which involves analyzing properties of a graph given memory that is sub-linear in the size of the stream. This problem is related to several areas of computer science, including data structures (cs.DS), discrete mathematics (cs.DM), computational complexity (cs.CC), social and information networks (cs.SI), and algorithms (cs.AL). Therefore, these are the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories for this paper.
